                  <td>14.5-15</td>
                  <td>18-24 months</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>18</td>
                  <td>26</td>
                  <td>9.5</td>
                  <td>17-17.5</td>
                  <td>2.5-3 years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>21</td>
                  <td>32</td>
                  <td>1.5</td>
                  <td>20-20.5</td>
                  <td>4-5 years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>25</td>
                  <td>39</td>
                  <td>5.5</td>
                  <td>24-24.5</td>
                  <td>6-7 years</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>30</td>
                  <td>45</td>
                  <td>11.5</td>
                  <td>29-29.5</td>
                  <td>9-10 years</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>

            <h2>Common Issues and Prevention</h2>
            
            <h3>Ingrown Toenails</h3>
            <p>
              Often caused by shoes that are too tight or pointed toe boxes. Prevention: 
              Proper fit with adequate toe space, straight-across nail trimming.
            </p>

            <h3>Flat Feet</h3>
            <p>
              Most children have flat feet until age 6-8 when arches develop. Most don't need 
              corrective footwear unless prescribed by a podiatrist. Flexible, lightweight shoes 
              support natural development.
            </p>

            <h3>Blisters and Calluses</h3>
            <p>
              Friction from poorly fitting shoes. Prevention: Smooth socks without seams, 
              proper shoe fit, breaking in new shoes gradually.
            </p>

            <h2>Manufacturing in China</h2>
            <p>
              China is the leading producer of children's shoes globally, with major production hubs:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Dongguan, Guangdong:</strong> Premium children's shoes for international brands</li>
              <li><strong>Wenzhou, Zhejiang:</strong> Large volume production, competitive pricing</li>
              <li><strong>Quanzhou, Fujian:</strong> Sports and athletic children's shoes</li>
              <li><strong>Baoding, Hebei:</strong> Leather children's shoes</li>
              <li><strong>Wenzhou, Zhejiang:</strong> PU and synthetic children's shoes</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Production Requirements</h3>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Material Testing:</strong> All materials must be tested for restricted substances</li>
              <li><strong>Physical Testing:</strong> Tensile strength, abrasion, flexibility tests</li>
              <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Full material disclosure for compliance verification</li>
              <li><strong>Packaging:</strong> No small parts in packaging; choking hazard warnings</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Sourcing Checklist</h2>
            <p>
              When sourcing children's shoes from China:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Verify material safety compliance for your target market</li>
              <li>Request full material breakdown and test reports</li>
              <li>Check factory certifications (ISO, BSCI, Sedex)</li>
              <li>Request samples in all size ranges</li>
              <li>Verify age-appropriate design features</li>
              <li>Confirm packaging compliance with toy safety regulations</li>
              <li>Include fitting guides and foot measurement charts with products</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <div class="space-y-8">
